						               													<description>Ruthless Merchants is a tabletop game in the pick up and deliver genre. The goal is simple, hold 5 coins at the end of a round and you win. You can choose to play peacefully and perform deliveries. Or you can play aggressively and punch/throw rocks at other players to get them to drop their coins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 6 characters you can choose to play. Move them around the marketplace and interact with other players. You can play one of six actions each turn. Move, pickup a coin or item, deliver an item to your destination for coins, punch a player, throw a rock at a player, or take a nap to remove your dizziness.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will need to balance between being peaceful and collecting your coins through deliveries and aggressively stealing other players coins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The fun of the action happens around the turn mechanic which determines the order of play. All players choose their action card, places it in a pile and then the pile is shuffled. Cards are dealt from the pile which determines the order of play. This means you can play a punch card, but your victim might move away from you before you can strike.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
